Assuming you have a User model and a Pub model, the next thing would be to create a relationship between them. A one to many relation would fit nicely here as a user can have one or more pubs but a pub can belong to a single user.

In User model
```
public function pubs()
    {
        return $this-&gt;hasMany(Pub::class);
    }
```

In Pub model
```
public function owner()
    {
        return $this-&gt;belongsTo(User::class);
    }
```

To retrieve pubs belonging to a user
```
